title: Grateful Dead Live at Music Hall on 1976-06-11
description:
Set 1

Might As Well, Mama Tried, Tennessee Jed, Cassidy, Candyman, Big River, Scarlet Begonias-> Looks Like Rain, It Must Have Been The Roses, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Brown Eyed Women, Promised Land

Set 2

Saint Stephen-> Dancin' In The Streets-> The Music Never Stopped, Ship of Fools, Samson & Delilah, Sugaree, Sugar Magnolia-> Eyes Of The World-> Stella Blue-> Sunshine Daydream, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: Nice upgrade Nice 2nd set improvement.  Full sound on this board.  Good solid playing too.  Very chilled out W. Coast vibe.  Enjoy

1976 is the most underrated year of touring Yes it all aligned in 77 
but this show is a prime example 
of the mojo of 1976.
This is the best year for 
Lightning-)Supplication
Also DJG breakout year.
She gets equal time with the boys
and proves she can handle whatever
Vocals come her way.
B.E Women in the first set
Stephen thru Dancin-)Music Set Two
Just gives the band added depth.
You can liken it to the way Phil gave 
the band vocal range when he sang on tunes like Jack Straw and while Phil gave them a baritone Donna is cross between  Loretta Lyn
and I don’t know Crystal Gale if she had tripped the light fantastic.
Also tunes like the Wheel and Help-) Slip-) Franklin’s bloom.
Scarlet Begonia’s has not been wedded to 🔥 
But since Scalet is still stand alone
there is plenty of room for
 its first set explorations 
which include some mesmerizing interplay 
between the band and DJG
I would like another 1000 words
But suffice it to say
Never had such a good time😛opener!
Does it work to split up Sugar from SsDd?

A very sweet SBD except.. My Lord! The boys sure did a LOT of tuning between songs to get everything "exactly right" Since I'm not a completist, I used Audacity to delete many minutes of crowd noise while keeping any banter and relevant tuning. I could also hear the whirr of the tape recorder (?) throughout all the quieter sections.
If not for those gripes, I'd give this show 5 Stars for when they were actually playing.
